14:30.437 --> 14:35.342
and I have done great work,
thanks to you.

14:35.408 --> 14:37.510
I've done it...

14:37.577 --> 14:38.945
behind the scenes, maybe,

14:38.946 --> 14:42.582
but I... I deserve
to be seen doing it.

14:42.649 --> 14:45.585
Shaken confidence
does not serve the client

14:45.652 --> 14:47.187
or the firm.

14:47.254 --> 14:50.190
My confidence is not shaken.

14:51.458 --> 14:52.458
Mine is.

15:00.600 --> 15:02.002
Come on.

15:04.471 --> 15:06.206
I'm ready for this.

15:08.441 --> 15:09.976
Let me do it.

15:09.977 --> 15:11.444
Please.

15:13.746 --> 15:16.984
You'll still be a valuable
member of the team.

15:19.486 --> 15:21.288
And a dear friend.

15:28.996 --> 15:30.630
Are you breaking up with me?

15:35.202 --> 15:36.503
- Good night.
- Good night.

15:41.008 --> 15:42.409
Callie.

15:42.475 --> 15:44.811
I hear you're back on top
with Borns Tech.

15:44.877 --> 15:46.446
Not surprising.
You always seem

15:46.513 --> 15:48.615
to get what you want in the end.

15:48.681 --> 15:51.384
The only thing I want
in the world is you.

15:51.451 --> 15:53.386
That's why...
why I texted Denise:

15:53.453 --> 15:55.053
because I want to be
a part of your life,

15:55.088 --> 15:57.490
- all parts of your life.
- Uh-huh.

15:57.557 --> 16:00.460
Well, your methodology
is disqualifying.

16:00.527 --> 16:02.429
I'm so... I'm s...

16:02.495 --> 16:03.230
I'm sorry...

16:03.296 --> 16:06.199
You traumatized my daughter.

16:06.266 --> 16:08.034
You traumatized me
in the process.

16:08.035 --> 16:09.369
We have no future together.

16:09.436 --> 16:13.506
If you never believe
anything I say again,

16:13.573 --> 16:14.574
believe that.

16:15.742 --> 16:16.742
Hey.

16:18.178 --> 16:19.612
If you care anything

16:19.679 --> 16:21.514
about what's left of your
little family unit,

16:21.581 --> 16:23.459
you might want to tell your
ex-husband to cry uncle

16:23.483 --> 16:26.186
because when I get done
with him...

16:26.253 --> 16:28.455
It's just difficult
to destroy dads

16:28.521 --> 16:31.091
without daughters becoming
collateral damage.

16:31.158 --> 16:34.061
Sometimes ex-wives, too.

16:36.696 --> 16:38.365
Fuck you.

16:51.411 --> 16:53.546
Finally. You get stuck
in the stairwell?

16:53.613 --> 16:54.981
Move.

16:55.082 --> 16:56.949
Let's look at the arrest report.

17:01.088 --> 17:02.689
Yeah. I'm on it.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.602
You did all this?

17:19.106 --> 17:20.640
It's impressive.

17:22.108 --> 17:24.777
I hope my daughters grow up
to be this capable.

17:29.716 --> 17:33.353
You're a great lawyer,
Lucy, with a great future.

17:35.788 --> 17:39.159
But not everybody is
cut out for trial work.

17:43.296 --> 17:44.764
Are you done with that?

18:00.313 --> 18:01.914
He did not!

18:01.981 --> 18:03.316
Hey.

18:03.383 --> 18:04.584
What do you want from me?

18:04.651 --> 18:05.818
Dad, it's me.

18:05.885 --> 18:06.995
I stuck out my neck for you.

18:07.019 --> 18:08.388
Now you live up...

18:09.822 --> 18:11.391
All right.

18:18.298 --> 18:19.832
What took you so long?

18:19.899 --> 18:21.568
They had to make the shit.

18:30.042 --> 18:35.014
Okay, so I got yours
with no onions.

18:35.081 --> 18:36.583
How you like it.

18:39.186 --> 18:41.554
Dad, you at least have
to take a bite of it.

18:41.621 --> 18:42.855
I will.

18:44.757 --> 18:46.426
You should call a doctor.

18:46.493 --> 18:48.528
I told you,
it's just a panic attack.

18:52.865 --> 18:54.834
You sure your mom's okay
with you staying here?

18:54.901 --> 18:57.069
Yeah, she seemed fine.

18:57.204 --> 18:58.505
Did you ask her?

18:59.972 --> 19:02.208
- No.
- That's what I thought.

19:02.209 --> 19:04.010
Well, she's been
really busy lately.

19:04.076 --> 19:05.612
She's on the phone
more than usual.

19:05.678 --> 19:08.748
How's your mom and, uh,
and your aunt Callie?

19:08.815 --> 19:09.882
How are they doing?

19:09.949 --> 19:12.619
Gross. I don't know. Okay?

19:12.685 --> 19:15.222
- I don't ask.
- I don't blame you.

19:17.557 --> 19:19.392
Can you watch anything else?

19:19.459 --> 19:22.395
Yeah. Rudy or High Noon.

19:30.503 --> 19:32.439
You sure you're okay?

19:32.505 --> 19:34.674
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

19:37.143 --> 19:39.279
Well, you look good.
So...

19:39.346 --> 19:42.582
Yeah, okay. Thanks.

19:47.487 --> 19:49.722
And for what it's worth,
I'm proud of you.

20:07.607 --> 20:09.409
♫ I don't like
staying at home ♫

20:09.476 --> 20:11.978
♫ When the moon
is bleeding red ♫

20:12.044 --> 20:13.913
♫ Woke up stoned
in a back seat ♫

20:13.980 --> 20:16.916
♫ From a dream where my
teeth fell out of my head ♫

20:16.983 --> 20:19.419
♫ Cut it up,
cut it up, yeah ♫

20:19.486 --> 20:21.688
♫ Everybody's
on something here ♫

20:21.754 --> 20:23.690
♫ My God, same chemical ♫

20:23.756 --> 20:26.693
♫ Best friend's skeleton
whispering in my ear ♫

20:26.759 --> 20:31.531
♫ Walk with me to the end ♫

20:31.598 --> 20:34.000
♫ Stare with me
into the aby... ♫

20:40.940 --> 20:42.475
Fuck.

20:43.776 --> 20:47.146
Hey. I thought it was you.
How are you? How's it...

20:47.213 --> 20:48.281
Let me see your license.

20:48.348 --> 20:50.216
Oh, come on.
You know who I am.

20:50.283 --> 20:52.352
Give me your license.

20:53.953 --> 20:59.326
Okay.

20:59.392 --> 21:00.727
Here you go.

21:03.896 --> 21:05.465
Brittany Gold.

21:06.466 --> 21:07.967
Get out of the car.

21:18.144 --> 21:19.712
I'm sorry about the tape.

21:19.779 --> 21:23.383
Don't worry. Billy won't
show it to anyone,

21:23.450 --> 21:25.352
especially not your wife.

21:25.418 --> 21:26.719
Karl Stoltz is dead.

21:26.786 --> 21:28.755
You know who that is, right?

21:28.821 --> 21:29.989
Did you really think

21:30.056 --> 21:32.058
I was going to let a bitch
like you set me up?

21:33.860 --> 21:34.861
I'm really sorry...

21:34.927 --> 21:35.962
You know what?

21:36.028 --> 21:37.464
I could run you in right now

21:37.530 --> 21:38.598
for the vials of shit

21:38.665 --> 21:40.008
that I know you have
on your person.

21:40.032 --> 21:41.368
- Fucking bitch!
- Aah!

21:48.575 --> 21:50.142
Chain in or out?

21:50.209 --> 21:52.044
In, please.

21:52.111 --> 21:53.646
All right, listen, I don't know

21:53.713 --> 21:55.415
who's going to be
there today, okay?

21:55.482 --> 21:57.149
- Yes.
- I need you on your A game.

21:57.216 --> 21:58.284
- All right?
- Okay.

21:58.385 --> 22:00.286
Laser focused. Okay?

22:00.387 --> 22:01.521
- Pee less.
- Right.

22:01.588 --> 22:03.131
Also, please learn
how to tie your own tie

22:03.155 --> 22:04.391
because you're
a grown-ass man.

22:04.457 --> 22:05.558
Oh, well.

22:05.625 --> 22:06.993
I'm so proud of you, sis.

22:07.059 --> 22:08.094
What are you...

22:08.160 --> 22:10.863
What the fuck is wrong with you?

22:10.930 --> 22:13.232
God damn it!

22:13.299 --> 22:15.468
Shit!

22:18.405 --> 22:20.507
Sorry I'm late. Traffic.

22:22.174 --> 22:23.410
Ready to go?

22:38.925 --> 22:40.827
♫ The city street is hot ♫

22:41.894 --> 22:45.765
♫ The heat has escalated ♫

22:45.832 --> 22:48.267
♫ Every corner in the town ♫

22:48.334 --> 22:51.438
♫ There's a paycheck ♫

22:51.504 --> 22:52.939
God damn it.

22:53.005 --> 22:56.142
♫ Well, they pretend
they like you ♫

22:56.208 --> 22:59.679
♫ But man's best friend
will bite you ♫

22:59.746 --> 23:02.582
♫ Just for fun ♫

23:04.050 --> 23:06.285
♫ If they're gunning
for you, boy ♫

23:06.352 --> 23:09.556
♫ You've already won ♫

23:13.159 --> 23:16.262
All right. This matter
is now in session.

23:16.328 --> 23:18.498
The Honorable
Rosten Keller presiding.

23:18.565 --> 23:19.732
Oh, here we go.

23:19.799 --> 23:22.301
The Estate of
Ryan Larson, et Al,

23:22.368 --> 23:24.604
versus Borns Technology.

23:24.671 --> 23:26.472
Parties are present, Your Honor.

23:26.473 --> 23:29.075
Be seated. Ahem.

23:30.276 --> 23:31.511
This matter is here

23:31.578 --> 23:33.245
for a status hearing.

23:33.312 --> 23:34.481
I'm looking at the file,

23:34.514 --> 23:38.117
but I see very little progress.

23:38.184 --> 23:39.218
I don't like that.

23:39.285 --> 23:40.520
Well, Your Honor,

23:40.587 --> 23:41.888
we've been conducting
depositions

23:41.954 --> 23:43.690
- and taking testimony...
- No.

23:43.756 --> 23:45.558
They've been doing depositions.

23:45.625 --> 23:47.259
In fact, from where I sit,

23:47.326 --> 23:49.729
you've done next to nothing
since we last convened

23:49.796 --> 23:51.831
other than show up
at my house uninvited.

23:51.898 --> 23:53.733
Your Honor,
it would take two years

23:53.800 --> 23:55.711
to go through all the
discovery they dumped on us,

23:55.735 --> 23:58.170
Plus, I'm dealing with
this police matter right now.

23:58.237 --> 23:59.539
It is not my concern.

23:59.606 --> 24:01.641
My concern is this case.

24:01.708 --> 24:04.343
You're not getting two years
to try this case.

24:04.410 --> 24:05.754
I'm not asking for that,
Your Honor.

24:05.778 --> 24:08.147
Listen, this case
either moves forward,

24:08.214 --> 24:10.216
or it stops.

24:10.282 --> 24:13.653
It's time to either put up
or shut up, counsel.

24:13.720 --> 24:15.655
What's it going to be?

24:21.661 --> 24:23.530
Did you hear me, sir?

24:23.563 --> 24:26.866
Yes, sir, I heard you.
Put up or shut up.

24:31.938 --> 24:33.940
The plaintiff chooses put up.

24:34.006 --> 24:36.108
I beg your pardon?

24:36.175 --> 24:38.210
We call ready for trial.

24:38.277 --> 24:39.411
What are you doing?

24:41.948 --> 24:44.884
We're not ready
for trial, Your Honor.

24:44.951 --> 24:47.153
Why not? You've got
about a million lawyers

24:47.219 --> 24:48.420
working on this.

24:48.555 --> 24:50.222
I call ready for trial.

24:50.289 --> 24:53.760
This is a dangerous game
you're playing, Mr. McBride.

24:53.826 --> 24:55.828
You haven't gone
through the discoveries.

24:55.895 --> 24:57.730
You haven't deposed
their witnesses.

24:57.797 --> 24:59.231
Well, I have a pretty good idea

24:59.298 --> 25:00.567
what they're gonna all say.

25:00.600 --> 25:02.044
Do I understand this correctly?

25:02.068 --> 25:04.837
You're ready to proceed
to trial now, today.

25:04.904 --> 25:06.906
Yes, sir, that's correct.

25:08.875 --> 25:10.843
- Miss Senate?
- This is ridiculous.

25:10.910 --> 25:12.578
If he says he's ready for trial,

25:12.579 --> 25:13.859
the court takes him at his word.

25:13.913 --> 25:15.181
This is a stunt.

25:15.247 --> 25:16.247
Your Honor,

25:16.282 --> 25:17.650
he is alleging negligence,

25:17.717 --> 25:19.585
which necessitates
more discovery

25:19.586 --> 25:21.153
with respect to duty of care.

25:21.220 --> 25:22.388
This will take time.

25:22.454 --> 25:23.823
Okay, let's forget negligence.

25:23.890 --> 25:26.158
We'll just go with
wrongful act and fraud.

25:26.225 --> 25:27.794
Excuse me? You're willing

25:27.860 --> 25:30.129
to waive the claims of
negligence against Borns Tech?

25:30.196 --> 25:31.363
That's correct.

25:31.430 --> 25:32.708
That's your strongest
cause of action.

25:32.732 --> 25:35.067
You open yourself up
to malpractice.

25:35.134 --> 25:37.670
Well, instead of going
with an innocent mistake,

25:37.737 --> 25:39.171
we're going to go
with a conspiracy.

25:39.238 --> 25:42.408
You're willing to waive
the negligence claim?

25:42.474 --> 25:43.943
I just did waive it.

25:44.010 --> 25:47.213
They say he killed himself.
We say he didn't.

25:47.279 --> 25:48.615
We say Borns Tech

25:48.681 --> 25:50.616
had him working
on an illegal weapon

25:50.617 --> 25:51.851
that blew him up.

25:51.918 --> 25:54.754
It's very simple.

25:54.821 --> 25:58.457
Your Honor, could I
have a moment to, uh...

25:58.524 --> 26:01.127
- Please.
- ...speak with my...

26:01.193 --> 26:02.194
people?

26:04.363 --> 26:05.765
Okay, thoughts?

26:05.832 --> 26:07.199
Nope, I don't like it.

26:07.266 --> 26:08.635
What are you talking about?

26:08.701 --> 26:10.036
There is no evidence

26:10.102 --> 26:13.039
of any intentional acts
or of a cover-up.

26:13.105 --> 26:16.843
If he's willing to go
with wrongful acts
and fraud, we win.

26:18.911 --> 26:19.846
Mm-mm.

26:19.912 --> 26:22.081
- Ahem.
- Counsel?

26:27.654 --> 26:28.855
Your Honor,

26:28.921 --> 26:31.090
we call ready for trial.

26:32.191 --> 26:33.192
Well,

26:33.259 --> 26:35.194
isn't this interesting?

26:36.829 --> 26:39.165
Call down the voir dire panel.

26:40.366 --> 26:42.669
We're gonna pick us a jury.

26:44.203 --> 26:45.672
What I don't understand

26:45.738 --> 26:47.339
is how you don't warn me.

26:47.406 --> 26:49.709
Well, you haven't been
listening to me.

26:49.776 --> 26:51.443
I wasn't sure
I was going to do it

26:51.510 --> 26:53.713
when we went in.
I had to see
if they were ready.

26:53.780 --> 26:55.047
We're not ready!

26:55.114 --> 26:56.749
- We're not ready.
- They're not, either.

26:56.816 --> 26:58.150
If they were ready,

26:58.217 --> 26:59.719
they would have
brought a whole crew

26:59.786 --> 27:01.053
and a bunch of video equipment,

27:01.120 --> 27:02.822
a bunch more files,
all kind of shit.

27:02.889 --> 27:04.824
So you in no way feel
that this is rushed.

27:04.891 --> 27:06.558
We have no choice.

27:06.693 --> 27:08.136
I mean, I could get
arrested any time.

27:08.160 --> 27:10.062
- Oh, stop.
- Or maybe killed.

27:10.129 --> 27:13.299
Jesus Christ.
Time's not exactly
on our side here.

27:15.267 --> 27:17.603
Tomorrow? Hmm.

27:17.704 --> 27:20.907
The partners
aren't happy, Donald.

27:20.973 --> 27:22.775
I wouldn't call it
exactly a revolt,

27:22.842 --> 27:24.376
but there's definite rumbling...

27:24.443 --> 27:26.746
mostly about the Borns Tech case

27:26.813 --> 27:28.715
and your relationship with Lucy.

27:28.781 --> 27:30.716
That's over,

27:30.717 --> 27:33.953
and the partners'
doubts will pass.

27:35.254 --> 27:36.254
Well...

27:37.724 --> 27:39.491
if...

27:39.558 --> 27:42.161
we win the Borns case, maybe.

27:42.228 --> 27:43.295
Or what?

27:44.931 --> 27:47.166
They'll replace me?

27:47.233 --> 27:50.102
I'd like to meet the man
they have in mind.

27:51.370 --> 27:52.772
Or the woman.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.744
Listen. Please
listen to me, Donald.

27:57.810 --> 27:59.311
People are concerned.

27:59.378 --> 28:03.149
You have been a rock...
stable, rational.

28:03.215 --> 28:06.118
This case has tripped
a wire somewhere.

28:08.220 --> 28:09.555
Ahem.

28:09.621 --> 28:10.790
Oh, my God.

28:10.857 --> 28:13.359
You are more like Billy
than you realize.

28:13.425 --> 28:16.162
You both need someone
to fight and to hate

28:16.228 --> 28:18.831
and to destroy.
You can't just be.

28:18.898 --> 28:20.666
I loved Billy.

28:20.767 --> 28:25.304
I truly did. Once.

28:27.439 --> 28:29.308
We were quite a team.

28:31.043 --> 28:33.245
You couldn't stand him, Donald.

28:33.312 --> 28:36.182
Eventually no, but in the
beginning I loved him.

28:36.248 --> 28:38.317
- Until you didn't.
- Until I didn't

28:38.384 --> 28:40.186
because he was weak,
because he drank,

28:40.252 --> 28:43.189
because he never really
stood for anything.

28:43.255 --> 28:44.957
That's what you do.

28:46.392 --> 28:47.960
People fall,

28:48.027 --> 28:50.062
and you just
let them keep falling.

28:50.129 --> 28:52.031
Oh, come on.

28:52.098 --> 28:54.200
Are you going to help Lucy?

28:54.266 --> 28:56.102
I know that you care about her.

28:56.168 --> 29:00.172
She just might be the one
thing to make you happy.

29:00.239 --> 29:01.507
She made me happy.

29:05.411 --> 29:07.079
But she was weak.

29:09.448 --> 29:10.516
Ahem.

29:16.823 --> 29:18.290
Lawyers are reminded...

29:18.357 --> 29:21.293
opening statements
are not arguments.

29:21.360 --> 29:23.495
They're road maps
to let the juries know

29:23.562 --> 29:25.998
what evidence they can
expect to hear.

29:26.065 --> 29:28.000
Plaintiff has
the burden of proof

29:28.067 --> 29:29.577
and delivers the first
opening statement.

29:29.601 --> 29:30.536
Cool.

29:30.602 --> 29:32.738
Um...

29:32.839 --> 29:34.173
okay, let's do this.

29:36.408 --> 29:37.910
How are you guys doing?

29:40.112 --> 29:43.049
Sorry. I had a little bit
of a kitchen accident.

29:43.115 --> 29:46.052
I was trying to get
an avocado pit out,

29:46.118 --> 29:48.888
and I did the stab method
instead of the chop.

29:48.955 --> 29:51.223
- Took off like half my...
- Ahem!

29:51.290 --> 29:52.892
...but I'm good to go.
I know. I'm here.

29:52.959 --> 29:54.760
I'm here, you're here.
Let's do this, right?

29:54.827 --> 29:56.728
So I am Patty Solis-Papagian.

29:56.795 --> 29:59.565
I represent Jason Larson.

29:59.631 --> 30:01.267
So two years ago,

30:01.333 --> 30:04.370
Ryan Larson, father of Jason,

30:04.436 --> 30:06.705
employee of Borns Tech,

30:06.772 --> 30:09.775
blew up on a boat
owned by the defendant.

30:09.842 --> 30:11.343
What was he doing on the boat?

30:11.410 --> 30:15.081
Well, he was dumping
explosives into the ocean.

30:15.147 --> 30:16.715
Completely illegal.

30:16.782 --> 30:18.550
Now, what were these explosives

30:18.617 --> 30:19.818
that he was dumping? Well,

30:19.886 --> 30:22.254
they were parts
of an illegal weapon

30:22.321 --> 30:24.756
that was being made
by Borns Tech.

30:24.823 --> 30:29.461
we have video of the explosion.

30:29.528 --> 30:31.030
Not only do we have video,

30:31.097 --> 30:32.831
we have the blueprints

30:32.899 --> 30:35.001
and the model of the weapon.

30:35.067 --> 30:39.105
We found them buried
in his backyard.

30:39.171 --> 30:41.840
Guy had them buried
in his backyard.

30:41.908 --> 30:43.842
At the end of the day,

30:43.910 --> 30:46.012
Borns Tech is no good.

30:46.078 --> 30:48.147
They're just no good

30:48.214 --> 30:50.716
because they do dangerous things

30:50.782 --> 30:52.184
with hazardous materials,

30:52.251 --> 30:53.920
and they don't care
who it affects.

30:53.953 --> 30:54.921
They could care less.

30:54.922 --> 30:56.088
And this is a trend

30:56.155 --> 30:58.257
that happens
with big corporations

30:58.324 --> 30:59.324
all the time.

30:59.358 --> 31:00.759
Your Honor?

31:00.826 --> 31:02.161
Ford with the Pinto,

31:02.228 --> 31:04.563
Big Tobacco, NFL with the...

31:04.630 --> 31:07.766
Those cases have nothing
to do with this case.

31:07.833 --> 31:10.536
The jury will disregard.

31:10.602 --> 31:11.737
Please disregard it.

31:11.803 --> 31:13.405
Please disregard it

31:13.472 --> 31:15.942
because that's
exactly what they do

31:16.008 --> 31:18.210
to people like you and me.
We are disregarded

31:18.277 --> 31:21.113
because, unless
