47:44.829 --> 47:45.997
Oh, okay.

47:46.064 --> 47:48.066
Yeah, and I
brought you something.

47:48.133 --> 47:50.135
- Really?
- Yeah.

47:50.201 --> 47:52.971
- For me, huh?
- Uh-huh. For you.

47:53.038 --> 47:54.639
Drum roll...

47:54.705 --> 47:56.975
♫ Da da da ♫

47:57.042 --> 47:58.944
Nice.

47:58.977 --> 48:01.546
With real cane sugar.
It's your favorite.

48:01.612 --> 48:03.014
Yeah, it's the real thing.

48:03.081 --> 48:04.682
It's warm, but it's still good.

48:04.749 --> 48:06.827
That's all right.
I'll put it in the fridge
in a little bit.

48:06.851 --> 48:08.653
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

48:11.356 --> 48:13.524
I thought today
went pretty good.

48:13.591 --> 48:14.592
Right?

48:20.131 --> 48:22.067
Anything I can do to help?

48:25.870 --> 48:27.238
Uh...

48:28.606 --> 48:30.275
shoot me.

48:30.341 --> 48:31.376
Come on.

48:33.844 --> 48:35.380
You're okay, right?

48:36.581 --> 48:37.615
Uh...

48:42.120 --> 48:44.122
I don't even know anymore.

48:47.425 --> 48:49.394
You're really good
at this, Billy.

48:51.029 --> 48:52.597
You're going to be great.

48:57.602 --> 48:59.170
Okay. well,
if you don't need me,

48:59.237 --> 49:00.438
then I got a date.

49:02.373 --> 49:04.609
So see you tomorrow.
Okay?

49:05.710 --> 49:06.710
Yeah.

49:09.714 --> 49:11.582
Good luck, baby.

49:14.385 --> 49:16.687
I thought you forgot
your charger.

49:16.754 --> 49:19.557
Oh. Yeah.

49:19.624 --> 49:21.626
I'm such an idiot, right?

49:21.692 --> 49:23.061
It's been a really long day.

49:23.128 --> 49:24.429
- Yeah.
- God.

49:25.496 --> 49:26.597
I hear you.

49:40.911 --> 49:41.846
Good morning.

49:41.912 --> 49:43.948
Good morning,
Mr. Corey.

49:44.049 --> 49:46.151
Wendell's fine.

49:47.118 --> 49:48.286
As I understand it,

49:48.353 --> 49:50.321
you make a lot of money
by killing people.

49:50.388 --> 49:52.657
We're defense contractors.

49:54.059 --> 49:55.226
We employ Americans

49:55.293 --> 49:57.995
that build the tools
to defend the country.

49:58.063 --> 50:00.331
Hmm. And you also
sell these tools

50:00.398 --> 50:02.367
to Russia and China
and Saudi Arabia

50:02.433 --> 50:04.069
and Yemen, places like that.

50:04.135 --> 50:05.836
If the price is right.

50:05.903 --> 50:07.648
The United States government
authorized those sales.

50:07.672 --> 50:10.141
A couple of those countries
are partners of ours

50:10.208 --> 50:11.542
in the war on terror.

50:11.609 --> 50:13.078
Now, part of this money you made

50:13.144 --> 50:14.779
came from the sale
of napalm, am I right?

50:14.845 --> 50:16.381
Napalm's not a banned weapon.

50:16.447 --> 50:18.416
If you use it
against civilians it is.

50:18.483 --> 50:20.151
We don't use it
against civilians.

50:20.218 --> 50:21.698
So you sell it
to a bunch of countries

50:21.752 --> 50:23.454
who do use it against civilians.

50:23.521 --> 50:25.156
- Objection.
- May I?

50:25.223 --> 50:26.623
This is all on public record.

50:26.657 --> 50:27.657
My aunt could find it.

50:27.692 --> 50:29.070
There's been another
partners meeting.

50:29.094 --> 50:30.228
- Sustained.
- Sustained?

50:30.295 --> 50:32.430
W-We were just talking
about this

50:32.497 --> 50:34.141
- two minutes ago.
- Those countries are not

50:34.165 --> 50:35.866
relevant to this case,
Mr. McBride.

50:35.933 --> 50:37.034
I was getting to something.

50:37.102 --> 50:39.036
Objection sustained.

50:39.104 --> 50:42.873
So, banned or not,
would you agree

50:42.940 --> 50:45.310
that it's illegal

50:45.376 --> 50:47.745
to test napalm off
the coast of Santa Monica?

50:47.812 --> 50:48.879
We don't do that.

50:48.946 --> 50:51.082
But you've done it in the past.

50:51.149 --> 50:53.918
You know what? A lot
of defense contractors

50:53.984 --> 50:55.853
tested various toxic materials

50:55.920 --> 50:57.388
in the past.
We don't do it now.

50:57.455 --> 50:59.690
Do you make cluster bombs?

50:59.757 --> 51:01.192
We're not licensed to, no.

51:01.259 --> 51:03.128
Okay. So in other words,
if you got caught

51:03.161 --> 51:04.595
making them or testing them,

51:04.662 --> 51:06.964
then you'd be fined
or go to prison or both.

51:07.031 --> 51:08.466
Objection.
Argumentative.

51:08.533 --> 51:10.635
You know what?
I already told you this.

51:10.701 --> 51:13.404
We never tested
or made them. Okay?

51:13.471 --> 51:16.941
Then why did Ryan Larson have
a model of a cluster bomb

51:17.007 --> 51:19.277
- buried in his backyard?
- Objection, Your Honor.

51:19.344 --> 51:21.746
- Lacks foundation.
- Sustained.

51:27.352 --> 51:28.919
Mr. Corey, all the rules

51:28.986 --> 51:33.524
about what fuel and weapons
can be made or tested

51:33.591 --> 51:35.393
are waived
during wartime, right?

51:35.460 --> 51:37.695
So our troops get all
the weapons they need

51:37.762 --> 51:38.896
to fight the bad guys.

51:38.963 --> 51:41.299
No. No. I mean,
a lot of them.

51:41.366 --> 51:45.035
Congress can pass what's
called a Wartime Suspension Act

51:45.170 --> 51:48.239
and give us room
to make what we need,

51:48.306 --> 51:51.175
regardless of the legal
ramifications, yeah.

51:51.176 --> 51:53.778
So hypothetically,
you could get a waiver

51:53.844 --> 51:55.780
to test napalm in the ocean

51:55.846 --> 51:57.315
or to build cluster bombs,

51:57.382 --> 51:58.659
even though that's
against the law.

51:58.683 --> 52:01.552
Hypothetically,
I suppose we could, yes.

52:01.619 --> 52:03.020
Who would apply
for those waivers?

52:03.087 --> 52:05.223
You and who else?

52:05.290 --> 52:06.757
Our lawyers.

52:06.824 --> 52:08.959
Hmm. So Mr. Letts
right here,

52:09.026 --> 52:10.328
Mr. Leonard Letts?

52:10.395 --> 52:12.697
Actually, no, not Mr. Letts.

52:12.763 --> 52:14.499
Well, he's your general counsel,

52:14.565 --> 52:16.367
so if it's not him, who is it?

52:17.935 --> 52:19.370
Donald Cooperman.

52:20.638 --> 52:23.208
- Donald Cooperman?
- Yeah.

52:23.274 --> 52:26.477
So if you wanted to get
one of these waivers

52:26.544 --> 52:30.047
to test napalm
or build a cluster bomb,

52:30.114 --> 52:32.049
who would you ask?

52:32.116 --> 52:33.751
Donald Cooperman.

52:33.818 --> 52:35.986
Did he ever allow Ryan Larson

52:36.053 --> 52:37.588
or anyone else at Borns Tech

52:37.655 --> 52:40.958
to design or make cluster bombs?

52:41.025 --> 52:42.227
I have no idea.

52:42.293 --> 52:44.795
Who would know?

52:44.862 --> 52:46.231
Donald Cooperman.

52:47.432 --> 52:48.966
Did a man named Karl Stoltz

52:49.033 --> 52:51.969
ever work for Borns Tech
or any of its subsidiaries?

52:52.036 --> 52:54.672
No. I mean,
not that I recall.

52:54.739 --> 52:56.641
Which one is it,
no or you don't recall?

52:56.707 --> 52:58.707
You know what? A lot of people
work for Borns Tech.

52:58.743 --> 53:01.246
Thousands. I can't
keep track of all of them,

53:01.279 --> 53:02.847
and I don't recognize that name.

53:02.913 --> 53:04.249
Hmm.

53:04.315 --> 53:06.083
Recognize that guy?

53:06.150 --> 53:08.786
No. Huh-uh.

53:11.256 --> 53:12.399
You're not looking at it, sir.

53:12.423 --> 53:14.058
- How would you know?
- Sure I am.

53:14.124 --> 53:17.628
Do you think it's possible
that he was a former Marine

53:17.695 --> 53:20.531
who worked for your
subsidiary in Dubai?

53:20.598 --> 53:23.868
Employee ID number 32823?

53:23.934 --> 53:25.270
Handled security over there,

53:25.336 --> 53:26.696
and then he came
back to the States

53:26.737 --> 53:29.139
- to work for you here?
- I don't have any idea.

53:29.274 --> 53:30.975
Who would know for sure?

53:31.041 --> 53:33.444
Main counsel
for personnel matters.

53:34.445 --> 53:36.013
Donald Cooperman.

53:36.080 --> 53:38.282
Once again, Donald Cooperman.

53:38.283 --> 53:41.486
Mr. McBride, do you
have any more questions
for this witness?

53:41.552 --> 53:43.521
Oh, no, Your Honor,
I don't. I'm sorry.

53:43.588 --> 53:46.290
I... I think he's said
all he's going to say.

53:46.291 --> 53:47.771
We just have one more
witness to call.

53:47.825 --> 53:49.960
We'd like to call Donald
Cooperman to the stand.

53:52.930 --> 53:54.299
Fuck.

53:57.802 --> 53:59.337
Jesus.

54:01.071 --> 54:03.741
Billy can't make you testify.

54:03.808 --> 54:07.445
The attorney-client privilege
absolutely prevents it.

54:07.512 --> 54:12.917
Well, Callie must have
showed him how,

54:12.983 --> 54:14.885
but Wendell opened the door.

54:14.952 --> 54:16.186
To what?

54:16.321 --> 54:18.323
He claims that I advised them

54:18.389 --> 54:19.924
that they could break the law.

54:19.990 --> 54:21.125
Did you?

54:21.191 --> 54:22.393
No.

54:25.095 --> 54:26.931
Doesn't matter.

54:26.997 --> 54:28.666
Does not matter.

54:28.733 --> 54:31.936
They cannot make you
get on that stand.

54:33.404 --> 54:36.707
Make me? Try to stop me.

54:43.348 --> 54:45.082
Me versus Billy.

54:45.149 --> 54:47.418
Once and for all.

54:50.355 --> 54:53.691
♫ Oh, where have you been ♫

54:53.758 --> 54:56.794
♫ Billy boy, Billy boy? ♫

54:57.862 --> 55:01.065
♫ Oh, where have you been... ♫

55:03.768 --> 55:05.503
♫ Charming Billy? ♫

55:06.837 --> 55:09.574
♫ I have been to seek a wife ♫

55:09.640 --> 55:13.978
♫ She's the joy of my life ♫

55:14.044 --> 55:18.916
♫ She's a young thing
and cannot leave her mother ♫

55:44.041 --> 55:45.275
Who is it?

55:45.410 --> 55:47.011
It's Callie.

55:56.787 --> 55:58.523
Hi, Billy.

55:58.589 --> 56:00.891
Hey. What's up?

56:03.260 --> 56:04.529
Am I interrupting?

56:04.595 --> 56:08.432
No. I was just playing
cards by myself here.

56:08.433 --> 56:10.435
Nothing too exciting.

56:11.769 --> 56:14.038
What, you're not going
to invite me in?

56:16.707 --> 56:18.443
Yeah, sure. Come on in.

56:24.649 --> 56:27.552
So this is the infamous
Ocean Lodge.

56:28.453 --> 56:29.687
Yeah, infamous

56:29.754 --> 56:32.289
is a pretty good way
to put it, I'll say.

56:32.356 --> 56:34.559
- Have a seat.
- No, I'm all right.

56:34.625 --> 56:36.126
I'm not staying.

56:36.193 --> 56:39.163
I just came to drop this off.

56:39.229 --> 56:41.131
Thought I would do it in person.

56:41.198 --> 56:43.133
Professional courtesy.

56:46.203 --> 56:47.672
Not anthrax, is it?

56:49.039 --> 56:50.541
It's our witness list.

56:53.243 --> 56:54.812
Good luck, Billy.

56:56.246 --> 56:57.482
Yeah, you, too.

58:57.267 --> 58:58.769
You stinker!

